      "body" : "If you read the quote above, it says it&#39;s constant-time &quot;assuming the hash function disperses the elements properly among the buckets&quot;. From CS theory, hash tables have constant time operations when the hash function is &quot;good&quot; (which happens on average), but may take linear time in the worst case."
